I remember looking down at the gauges on the banks of Daytona in NASCAR turn 2 during my race…..watching the odometer turn over 77,000 miles and thinkin “that’s pretty neat!” Oh the stories this bike would tell around a campfire at midnight.  Absolutely there is No other bike out there quite like this one.  If I only would have known the day I brought this bike home how much it would steer my life in a different direction.  All the miles, memories, challenges, lessons and friends made.  It’s been more than just a motorcycle….it’s been a hell of a ride.
The safest bet in life is knowing that your never safe.  A little metal graining on @screaminspeednfab side covers.

Well @musiccityindian in Nashville TN didn’t want @forever_rad_ to have all the fun on the brand new challengers.  They got me on a ‘23 @indianmotorcycle Challenger Dark Horse.  Excited to smash some miles and throw my flavor at this thing.  We know I can’t keep anything stock. Already have some @smtwheels on order and barnstormcycles dash kit via foreverrad.com to run t-bars and @beringerbrakes_usa hand controls. Time to ride these babies home from Nashville! So stoked.

Nothing better than new bike day.  But when you get that New @indianmotorcycle from @kamtheindianguy of @musiccityindian in Nashville and then you can ride it home 300 miles in the sunshine in January with your homie @forever_rad_ by your side.  Yea that’s a pretty epic day
Excited for many road trips this summer on the @indianmotorcycle challenger.

Excited to announce that @bareknuckleperformance and I had a meeting for the race season and he will continue to help for the 2023 @baggerracingleague season. I currently run his cinch fork brace and stainless front axle.  This definitely noticeably tightened up my front end especially with the amount of lift I run up front.  And it just is the cleanest setup out there in my opinion. We also did some trading for some of my @screaminspeednfab side covers for an upcoming project of his and I got a 2” suspension lift for my new indian challenger he makes!  So I just want to say thanks to Paul for the support cause we all know racing isn’t cheap and buying a set of tires or a hotel for the night goes a long way. 🤘🤘#supportthosewhosupportyou #baggerracing #fast #livingmybestlife

Soooo it begins.  Got some parts to install on this @indianmotorcycle Challenger. @musiccityindian and @forever_rad_  getting the parts on the way to get this thing comfy and faster! P.S.  subscribe to my YouTube schamberlin5150. We’re starting the series back up this summer after a 1 year plus hiatus.
Ready to do all the road trips on this thing this summer!!

These @speeddealer Harley bagger swingarms are no joke!  Such beautiful craftsmenship from front to back, inside and out.  Stoked to own one of these beautiful pieces!! @noori_alicia in the black and gold.  Mine in Natural and black.  And @getbentmoto in the Polished and Gold!

Well we’ve had the Indian Challenger for about 3 weeks now and we are ready for Daytona bike week with it unless our @smtwheels 19-18 wheel combo and @dtf_speedandperformance smooth carbon fiber Indian rear fender come in before then we’ll slap those on. Tbars with @beringerbrakes_usa hand controls✅ @bareknuckleperformance lift✅ @forever_rad_/ @prior_performance lp6 kit.✅ @klockwerks dynamat/11” shield.✅ Stage 2 cams from @musiccityindian ✅ and a bunch more things. ✅ Can’t wait to smash some miles on this thing after I get a tune one Tuesday!
Do whatever you want to do in life.  But make it count……every damn day.

Shoutout to @smtwheels on the new pit rug for racing!! But first a backstory When I first got into racing Harley baggers I still wanted to go in between my street and race wheels.  Talked to @martin_smt_wheels about getting a set of 17” wheels made with lightened hubs and custom stepped lip to reduce weight with about a 5 week time window. (He even windowed the Cush drive) So I could swap back and forth between street wheels and track wheels.  The fitment was absolutely perfect.  The finish was amazing. Arp bolts holding the hubs together as well as pinned.  And after countless wheelies, races, and 2 crashes they still holding up like brand new.  When you want the best without the bullshit and honest leadtimes. SMT is your answer. Thanks again Martin and your team!  So if you made it to the end of this let’s do a little giveaway on me.  I will buy you one of these rugs and a SMT Racing Shirt and also get you a @screaminspeednfab racing shirt and a Banner. A comment thread is your entry and must follow @smtwheels before winning or I will pick a new winner. I’ll pick a winner at 6pmish central Sunday 2-19
@forever_rad_ @screaminspeednfab catch this one in Daytona bike week.

Well here she is…..Daytona ready.  Riding it the 1k miles to Daytona starting tomorrow.  We picked up this @indianmotorcycle 2023 Challenger darkhorse from @musiccityindian  January 17.  Quickly tore into it with the help of @forever_rad_  and installed the stage 2 cams and a custom coated air cleaner. barnstormcycles tbar relocation setup with  @rolandsandsdesign risers and @beringerbrakes_usa brake master and clutch lever, fly bars and some @motogadget mirrors. An 8” clear @klockwerks windshield and dynamat inside the fairing.  Movin on to the exhaust we installed a 2-1 bassani pipe but swapped out to a shorter muffler with the help of the @cmpmc bag bracket kit as the stock bags are supported by the dual mufflers.  @saddlemen slim seat. Then the back end of this bike was overly red in my opinion so we opted for the @dtf_speedandperformance smooth carbon fiber rear fender that we chopped about 3” off the back and carbon fiber tank dash. Cmp plate mount. @bareknuckleperformance 2” lift front and rear.  Gloss blacked the swingarm since it was way more visible. Then @prior_performance floorboards and pegs made For Indians. Then to wrap it up we did the first set of @forever_rad_ FTR fender brackets, Baja lp6 headlight kit.  We will have his bag latch covers in a custom anodized black installed in daytona for the cherry on top. See y’all out there soon!  We got ourself a mile crushing ripper!!

Well with about 2k miles on this new challenger I’m here to hit ya with a review.  Plain and simple if this bike had a Harley logo instead of the indian on the side of the tank y’all would be ranting and raving how it’s the greatest touring vtwin bike ever.  Plain and simple.  And with the little money I’ve throw at this one to be cool.  I would say throw 30k at a roadglide to make it perform as well as this one does.  Next so I don’t have to keep repeating myself.  Yes I will continue to race my roadglide in bagger racing league.  We are in Pittsburg in may and Illinois in July California after that.  No I don’t know what other events I’ll be doing this year yet for sure.  Possibly some motoamerica events.  Have some big trips planned on the Challenger as I now have a fun and comfortable trip bike.  Yes Business has been good and we got more cookin up so stay tuned.  2023 is going to be a great year for more riding!! 🤘😆🤘

After putting about 3k miles on this @musiccityindian Challenger I’m so ready for some good road trips this summer.  What are y’all planning on doing and when is it.  Last summer with the Harley I managed to put it on the podium at BRL twice and do a 2800 mile round trip to sturgis and a couple other trips.  Trying to hold that fine line between having a racebike and a road bike is extremely stressful so I’m stoked to have this new ripper @indianmotorcycle to smash some miles on.  Just need a Lloyd’s tune that I’ll get from @forever_rad_  and @smtwheels 19/18” wheel combo with their rotors and ill be beyond stoked on this thing for the summer! #performancebagger

What a hell of a weekend at @baggerracingleague pittrace.  The track was incredible and had its fair share of challenges.  Today the weather took a turn and we all had to race in the rain in pro stock bagger.  I have never raced or rode on rain tires.  The grip you still have is insane.  I was battling my helmet shield fogging up for most of the race.  Went off track and got squirley twice. Holding my helmet up and taking rain drops to the eyeballs at 100 plus so I ended up mistaking the last lap flag for the checkered flag and pulled off early.  My mistake.  But all in all.  Great weekend with everyone and the help for everyone at the track all around.  If you haven’t tried this yet you are missing out.  Thanks for all those who came out and all those who support.  See y’all At Blackhawk farms in July.

I truly think the biggest problem in this day and age is people don’t travel….well travel the less traveled path.  When you get out off the expressways and out of the airports that get you from Point A to Point B as fast as possible.  I’m going to encourage you this year to get on the path less traveled.  Get uncomfortable. Go to that diner in the middle of nowhere.  Hold that random 20 min conversation with a gas clerk.  Go the long way around the lake.  Learn that not everyone in this life will live it the same.

Well day started early to head out to the Smokey mountains with @forever_rad_ and @frankiedooks  Found a nail in my tire on the indian yesterday and decided to throw a plug in it and run it.  Made it about 45 miles and boom tire went flat.  It chucked the plug.  While attempting to throw in a new plug we noticed the belt was missing an assortment of teeth. So we decide to head back. 2nd plug fell out in about 15 miles. Threw a double plug in and made it back.  Spent about 20 mins throwing the sissybar and hardware and a phone mount on the race bike and headed back out and smashed 500 miles on it.  No bad days allowed.
I think Y’all ought to get back on your bikes and ride the highway until you remember what riding is all about. #smokeymountains #performancebagger #wildhogs
Rollin out #performancebagger

After only putting about 200 miles on this bike in the past 12 months cause it has stayed in race trim it felt good to smash over 1900 miles on it in 6 days. From race trim to street trim I swapped to stock wheels and @bareknuckleperformance rotors and fresh cruisetec tires.  And also swapped from the speed merchant mids to some @arlennessmotorcycles ones and @prior_performance mini boards for a bit more legroom.  Gunna throw a couple more street miles on it then swap back to race trim and head to the @baggerracingleague final round at willow springs.  What a killer weekend in the smokies. 📸 @vbag258

IT’S RACE WEEK BABY!  About to leave to head to Cali to race @baggerracingleague at Willow Springs this weekend.  Let’s freakin go for the last race of the season!! If anybody wants to help support the underdog. Dm for PayPal, Applepay, or buy some products I build off screaminspeednfab dot com.  Cool thanks!

What a hell of a weekend with @baggerracingleague.  I took my true prostock, street legal, pump gas bagger (that I roadtripped 1900 miles just last month) and took it to a solid 5th place finish!  I am super stoked on that as this is what this class is about!  Thank you to all that showed up, showed out and had a good time!  Now gimme 20 mins and a couple hand tools and I can road-trip this same bike back 1750 miles home.  Thank you for the support in the pits / at the track from @laurafeasler @ride.fast.take.chances @forever_rad_ @santorofabworx @lexinmoto @beringerbrakes_usa @geezerengineering @a_plus_performance_cycle @shredderbob_racing  @bareknuckleperformance @prior_performance
